we have an react design system called `'@otovo/rainbow'` please create some stubs for it where I can start defining types for it.

I'll help you create type declaration stubs for `@otovo/rainbow`. Let's create a basic structure that you can expand upon:

```typescript
// @types/otovo__rainbow/index.d.ts

declare module '@otovo/rainbow' {
  import { ComponentProps, ReactNode, ElementType } from 'react'

  // Common prop types
  interface BaseProps {
    className?: string;
    children?: ReactNode;
  }

  // Box component
  export interface BoxProps extends BaseProps {
    as?: ElementType;
    padding?: number | string;
    margin?: number | string;
    display?: 'block' | 'flex' | 'inline' | 'inline-block' | 'grid';
    alignItems?: 'flex-start' | 'center' | 'flex-end' | 'stretch';
    justifyContent?: 'flex-start' | 'center' | 'flex-end' | 'space-between';
    flexDirection?: 'row' | 'column';
    gap?: number | string;
  }
  export const Box: React.FC<BoxProps>;

  // Button component
  export interface ButtonProps extends BaseProps {
    variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'tertiary' | 'danger';
    size?: 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';
    disabled?: boolean;
    onClick?: () => void;
    type?: 'button' | 'submit' | 'reset';
    loading?: boolean;
  }
  export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps>;

  // Typography components
  interface TypographyProps extends BaseProps {
    color?: string;
    align?: 'left' | 'center' | 'right';
  }

  export const H1: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const H2: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const H3: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const H4: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const H5: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const H6: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const Text: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const BodyM: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const BodyS: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const CaptionM: React.FC<TypographyProps>;
  export const CaptionS: React.FC<TypographyProps>;

  // Form components
  export interface InputFieldProps extends ComponentProps<'input'> {
    label?: string;
    errorMessage?: string;
    showValidation?: boolean;
  }
  export const InputField: React.FC<InputFieldProps>;

  export interface FormProps extends ComponentProps<'form'> {
    onSubmit?: (e: React.FormEvent) => void;
  }
  export const Form: React.FC<FormProps>;

  // Toggle component
  export interface ToggleProps {
    checked?: boolean;
    onChange?: (checked: boolean) => void;
    disabled?: boolean;
    label?: string;
  }
  export const Toggle: React.FC<ToggleProps>;

  // Badge component
  export interface BadgeProps extends BaseProps {
    variant?: 'default' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'error';
  }
  export const Badge: React.FC<BadgeProps>;

  // Link component
  export interface LinkProps extends BaseProps {
    href?: string;
    external?: boolean;
    underline?: boolean;
  }
  export const Link: React.FC<LinkProps>;

  // ErrorMessage component
  export interface ErrorMessageProps extends BaseProps {
    message?: string;
  }
  export const ErrorMessage: React.FC<ErrorMessageProps>;
}
```

To use these type definitions, you'll need to:

1. Create a `@types` folder in your project root (if it doesn't exist already)
2. Create an `otovo__rainbow` folder inside it
3. Add the above code in an `index.d.ts` file

The folder structure should look like this:
```
project-root/
  @types/
    otovo__rainbow/
      index.d.ts
```

Then add this to your `tsconfig.json`:
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "typeRoots": ["./node_modules/@types", "./@types"]
  }
}
```

You can then expand these type definitions as needed by:
1. Adding more components
2. Adding more specific prop types
3. Adding proper event handler types
4. Adding more specific style prop types

