I'll help you set up the TypeScript configuration for your monorepo. Here's a suggested structure for each tsconfig file:

```json
// Root tsconfig.json (base configuration)
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020",
    "module": "ESNext",
    "lib": ["DOM", "DOM.Iterable", "ESNext"],
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "allowImportingTsExtensions": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "noEmit": true,
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "strict": true,
    "noUnusedLocals": true,
    "noUnusedParameters": true,
    "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true,
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@otovo/*": ["packages/*"]
    }
  },
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}

// @otovo/shared/tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "composite": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationMap": true
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "references": []
}

// breeze/tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../@otovo/shared" }
  ]
}

// my-page/tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../@otovo/shared" }
  ]
}

// storefront/tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../@otovo/shared" }
  ]
}
```

Additionally, you might want a tsconfig.build.json in the root for building all projects:

```json
// tsconfig.build.json
{
  "files": [],
  "references": [
    { "path": "./@otovo/shared" },
    { "path": "./breeze" },
    { "path": "./my-page" },
    { "path": "./storefront" }
  ]
}
```

You can then build the entire project using:
```bash
tsc -b tsconfig.build.json
```

This setup:
1. Uses project references
2. Allows sharing types between projects
3. Maintains independent compilation
4. Shares common configuration from the root
5. Enables incremental builds

