should we move these to the type def file?
Yes, these types should be moved to the type definition file we were creating earlier, especially since they define the core styling props for the Rainbow design system. Let's adapt our earlier type definition file to include these:

```typescript
// @types/otovo__rainbow/index.d.ts

declare module '@otovo/rainbow' {
  import { ComponentProps, ReactNode, ElementType } from 'react'

  type Rainbow$BreakpointArray = Array<string | number>;
  type Rainbow$BreakpointObject = {
    s?: string | number;
    s2?: string | number;
    s3?: string | number;
    m?: string | number;
    m2?: string | number;
    m3?: string | number;
    l?: string | number;
    l2?: string | number;
    l3?: string | number;
  };

  export type Rainbow$Prop =
    | string
    | number
    | Rainbow$BreakpointObject
    | Rainbow$BreakpointArray;

  // [... all the other type definitions from rainbow.ts ...]

  export type Rainbow$Props = Rainbow$MarginProps &
    Rainbow$PaddingProps &
    Rainbow$ColorProps &
    Rainbow$TypographyProps &
    Rainbow$LayoutProps &
    Rainbow$FlexProps &
    Rainbow$GridProps &
    Rainbow$BackgroundProps &
    Rainbow$BorderProps &
    Rainbow$PositionProps &
    Rainbow$ShadowProps &
    Rainbow$MiscProps;

  // Component interfaces that use these types
  interface BaseProps extends Rainbow$Props {
    className?: string;
    children?: ReactNode;
  }

  export interface BoxProps extends BaseProps {
    as?: ElementType;
  }
  export const Box: React.FC<BoxProps>;

  // ... rest of component definitions ...
}
```

This would:
1. Move the types to the central type definition file
2. Make them available to all components in the design system
3. Allow you to remove the deprecated file
4. Maintain type consistency across the design system

